snippet.textDisplay: This... is so sad. Yoongi was legit the most perfect choice for this song out of all the members due to his known depression and struggle with the self. I know a lot of people are saying that the line “don’t let me fly” is his shadow speaking but I don’t think it is, I don’t think any lines are by his shadow till his shadow actually appears which is the yoongi in the crowd. I think the lyrics of his shadow growing into a monster is his persona fearing his shadow and and the persona is also the one saying “don’t let me shine, don’t let me fly” as that will mean his shadow will reappear. That’s just my theory anyway. Furthermore I love how someone said this isn’t Suga or Agust D. This is Min Yoongi, as a person, as a soul. BTS did say that the LY era was about sending a message out to Army but that the MOTS Era is about themselves, as human beings struggling to navigate the whirlwind of their life and fame and sense of self.
snippet.textOriginal: This... is so sad. Yoongi was legit the most perfect choice for this song out of all the members due to his known depression and struggle with the self. I think the lyrics of his shadow growing into a monster is his persona fearing his shadow and and the persona is also the one saying “don’t let me shine, don’t let me fly” as that will mean his shadow will reappear. That’s just my theory anyway. Furthermore I love how someone said this isn’t Suga or Agust D. This is Min Yoongi, as a person, as a soul. BTS did say that the LY era was about sending a message out to Army but that the MOTS Era is about themselves, as human beings struggling to navigate the whirlwind of their life and fame and sense of self.
